@page "/"

<PageTitle>WitDatabase Blazor WASM Sample</PageTitle>

<div class="card">
    <h1>&#128190; WitDatabase Blazor WASM Sample</h1>
    <p>
        This sample demonstrates using <strong>WitDatabase</strong> in a Blazor WebAssembly application.
        Uses async initialization via <code>BuildAsync()</code> for WASM compatibility.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card" style="background: #fff3cd; border-color: #ffc107;">
    <h3>?? Work in Progress: IndexedDB Support</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Current Status:</strong> In-memory storage works fully. IndexedDB storage initialization works,
        but data operations (Put/Get/Delete) require full async BTree refactoring which is in progress.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>What works now:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>? In-memory storage (full functionality)</li>
        <li>? BTree async initialization</li>
        <li>? Transactions</li>
        <li>? Encryption (AES-GCM)</li>
        <li>? IndexedDB persistence (initialization only, data ops in progress)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        See <a href="https://github.com/dmitrat/WitDatabase/blob/main/Docs/TODO-BTree-Async-Refactoring.md" target="_blank">TODO-BTree-Async-Refactoring.md</a> for the full refactoring plan.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h3>Features Demonstrated</h3>
    
    <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="crud">CRUD Operations</a></strong> - Basic Create, Read, Update, Delete operations</li>
        <li><strong><a href="transactions">Transactions</a></strong> - Transaction support with commit/rollback</li>
        <li><strong><a href="encryption">Encryption</a></strong> - AES-GCM encryption at rest</li>
    </ul>
</div>

